\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} a_nz^n
a_0=1,a_1=-1
3a_n+4a_{n-1}-a_{n-2}=0
n>1
a_n = A r^n
r
3 r^2 + 4 r - 1=0
r = (-2 \pm \sqrt{7})/3
a_n = A \left (\frac{\sqrt{7} - 2}{3} \right )^n +  B (-1)^n \left (\frac{\sqrt{7} + 2}{3} \right)^n 
\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} a_n z^n = A \frac{3}{3-(\sqrt{7} - 2) z} + B \frac{3}{3+(\sqrt{7} + 2) z} 
|z| \le R = \frac{3}{\sqrt{7} + 2} = \sqrt{7} - 2 
a_n=\lambda^n
\lambda
3\lambda^2+4\lambda-1=0
\lambda=\frac{-2\pm\sqrt 7}3
\alpha,\beta
a_0, a_1
\alpha
\beta
0
a_n=\alpha\left(\frac{-2+\sqrt 7}3\right)^n+\beta \left(\frac{-2-\sqrt 7}3\right)^n
 \limsup_{n\to\infty}\sqrt[n]{|a_n|}=\max\left\{\left|\frac{-2+\sqrt 7}3\right|,\left|\frac{-2-\sqrt 7}3\right|\right\}
